@node "AMosaic" "Using Pine with a Web Browser"
New with this release is the use of Pine with any web browser that supports
mailto:'s. Listed below are all the browsers known to date and instructions
on how to set up Pine for them.

@{b}AMosaic@{ub}
All you have to do is @{b}setenv Mosaic/EDITOR pine:pine -amosaic@{ub}.
(NOTE that this has changed from previous releases).Now when you click on an URL,
Pine pops up in the COMPOSE MESSAGE screen with the address in the To: field.

@{b}AWeb@{ub}
Use the AWebSendMail.rexx file included in the base archive. Look at the source
to see how to set up AWeb to use the script.

@{b}Voyager@{ub}
Go to the Setting menu and choose Network. Click on other and click on the mailto:
string gadget. Type in "pine:pine <>CON://640/256/Pine/SCREEN* %h" (without the
quotes of course) and click on use.

@{b}IBrowse@{ub}
Since the last few versions of IBrowse doesn't support mailto: I have no
instructions at this time.
@endnode

@node "Spruce" "Be on the lookout for Spruce"
After Pine was released, people have been bugging me to make a full GUI
version. Your wish is my command! Spruce (named after a defunct UNIX GUI
version of Pine) will maintain full Pine compatibility along with the
following features:
 Font sensitivity
 Automatic window reconstruction on resize
 No MUI!
 Will make use of a new ixemul.library with network support. Maybe I will
 port Spruce to SAS/C at a later date.

To get a preview of Spruce. Point your web browser to
@{b}http://www.undergrad.math.uwaterloo.ca/~jsshephe/spruce.html@{ub},
You will find a Spruce beta release there.
@endnode

@node "homepage" "Yes Pine now has a homepage"
I finally set up a homepage for Pine. It can be reached off of my homepage at
@{b}http://www.undergrad.math.uwaterloo.ca/~jsshephe/pine.html@{ub}.
While you are there you can also check out another project I am working on
@{"Spruce" link "Spruce" 0}
@endnode

